{"title_page": "NOTD", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = NOTD\n| background = group_or_band\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| alias = \n| origin = \n| genre = \n| years_active = {{start date|2017}}\u2013present\n| label = [[Universal Music Group]]<ref name=\"universal music\">{{cite web |title=NOTD DROP THE OFFICIAL VIDEO FOR BEA MILLER COLLABORATION \"I WANNA KNOW\" {{!}} Umusic |url=http://www.umusic.ca/press-releases/notd-drop-official-video-bea-miller-collaboration-wanna-know/ |website=Umusic |accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref>\n| associated_acts = [[Dagny (singer)|Dagny]] <br> [[Bea Miller]] <br> [[Tove Styrke]]\n| website = \n| current_members =\n* Samuel Brandt (Severo)\n* Tobias Danielsson (ToWonder)\n| past_members    = <!--listed in order of joining per Template:Infobox Musical artist (Boyd/Gray/LeCompt alphabetical by surname\u2014joined at the same time)-->\n}}\n\n'''NOTD''' (pronounced \"noted\") <!--according to iTunes referenced at the end of this sentence--> is a musical production duo from Sweden composed of Tobias Danielsson and Samuel Brandt.<ref name=\"itunes bio\">{{cite web |title=I Wanna Know (feat. Bea Miller) by NOTD |url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/i-wanna-know-feat-bea-miller/1357067762?i=1357067766 |accessdate=18 June 2018 |date=16 March 2018}}</ref> They are best known for their songs \"[[I Wanna Know (NOTD song)|I Wanna Know]]\" featuring [[Bea Miller]] and \"[[So Close (NOTD song)|So Close]]\" with [[Felix Jaehn]] featuring [[Captain Cuts]] and [[Georgia Ku]].\n\n==Background==\nThe duo met on [[SoundCloud]] and began creating remixes together before they found out they would be attending the same high school.<ref name=\"prelude\">{{cite web |last1=Vigil |first1=Dom |title=NOTD releases \"I Wanna Know\" Featuring Bea Miller Remixes |url=https://thepreludepress.com/news/2018/4/27/notd-releases-i-wanna-know-featuring-bea-miller-remixes |website=The Prelude Press |accessdate=20 June 2018}}</ref> The duo chose the name NOTD by combining the last two letters of each of their last names and reversing them.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Espiritu |first1=Camille |title=Music Interview: NOTD - The Young Folks |url=https://www.theyoungfolks.com/music/123134/music-interview-notd/ |website=www.theyoungfolks.com |accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nTheir remix of \"[[Scars to Your Beautiful]]\" by [[Alessia Cara]] was released in 2016.<ref name=\"alessia cara remix\">{{cite web |last1=Bein |first1=Kat |title=Alessia Cara's 'Scars to Your Beautiful' Remixes: Listen to the 7 Best |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7684974/alessia-cara-best-remixes-list |website=Billboard |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> A remix of \"[[Dark Side (Phoebe Ryan song)|Dark Side]]\" by [[Phoebe Ryan]] was released in 2017.<ref name=\"phoebe ryan\">{{cite web |last1=Murray |first1=Robin |title=Premiere: Phoebe Ryan - 'Dark Side' (NOTD Remix) |url=http://clashmusic.com/news/premiere-phoebe-ryan-dark-side-notd-remix |website=Clash Magazine |accessdate=18 June 2018 |language=en}}</ref> Their remix of STANAJ's \"Romantic\", which peaked at #91 in Australia (as \"The Preview EP\") was released on 27 January 2017.<ref>{{Citation|title=Stanaj \u2013 Romantic (NOTD Remix)|url=https://genius.com/Stanaj-romantic-notd-remix-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2018-10-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=48692&pages=5|title=australian-charts.com - Forum - ARIA Chartifacts 17-April-2017|date=17 April 2017|website=australian-charts.com|access-date=2018-10-24}}</ref>  Their remix of \"[[There's Nothing Holdin' Me Back]]\" by [[Shawn Mendes]] was released in May 2017. Their remix of \"[[Shape of You]]\" by [[Ed Sheeran]] received a nomination for an [[Electronic Music Awards|Electronic Music Award]] for Remix of the Year.<ref name=\"edm award\">{{cite web |last1=Rishty |first1=David |title=The Chainsmokers, Justice, Eric Prydz & More Nominated for 2017 Electronic Music Awards |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7896929/electronic-music-awards-nominees-complete-list-2017 |website=Billboard |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> Also in 2017, they released a remix of \"[[Wild Thoughts]]\" by [[DJ Khaled]] and [[Rihanna]], which appeared on Billboard's list of the best remixes of the song.<ref name=\"wild thoughts remix\">{{cite web |last1=Finkelstein |first1=Sabrina |title=The 5 Best DJ Khaled 'Wild Thoughts' Remixes |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7873774/dj-khaled-wild-thoughts-remixes-best |website=Billboard |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> They released their debut single \"Summer of Love\" which features Norwegian singer [[Dagny (singer)|Dagny]] on 11 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rogers |first1=Mandy |title=Listen to \"Summer of Love\" by NOTD ft Dagny - EQ Music Blog |url=https://eqmusicblog.com/listen-summer-love-notd-ft-dagny/ |website=EQ Music Blog |accessdate=10 July 2018 |date=15 August 2017}}</ref> In December 2017, they released a remix of \"[[Tell Me You Love Me (song)|Tell Me You Love Me]]\" by [[Demi Lovato]].<ref name=\"demi lovato\">{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Demi Lovato's \"Tell Me You Love Me\" Gets A Dance Remix From NOTD |url=http://www.idolator.com/7672662/demi-lovato-tell-me-you-love-me-notd-remix?chrome=1 |website=idolator |accessdate=18 June 2018 |date=15 December 2017}}</ref> They also produced a remix of [[Years & Years]]' song \"[[If You're Over Me]]\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Herman |first1=Tamar |title=SHINee's Key Joins Years & Years on Epic 'If You're Over Me' Remix: Listen |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8464216/shinee-key-years-years-if-youre-over-me-remix |website=Billboard |accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nTheir second single \"I Wanna Know\" featuring [[Bea Miller]] was released in March 2018.<ref name=\"fuse\">{{cite web |last1=Gracie |first1=Bianca |title=NOTD & Bea Miller's Moody 'I Wanna Know' Collaboration Is All About Summer Blues: Premiere |url=https://www.fuse.tv/videos/2018/03/notd-bea-miller-i-wanna-know-single-premiere |website=Fuse |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> The song charted in several countries, including [[Australia]], [[Canada]], and [[Sweden]]. Their single \"Been There Done That\" with [[Tove Styrke]] was released in August.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bein |first1=Kat |title=NOTD & Tove Styrke Are Stuck on Love With 'Been There Done That': Listen |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8472119/notd-tove-styrke-been-there-done-that |website=Billboard |accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe duo and [[Felix Jaehn]] released the single \"[[So Close (NOTD and Felix Jaehn song)|So Close]]\", with a music video starring [[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue|''Sports Illustrated'' Swimsuit]] cover girl [[Camille Kostek]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8517789/notd-felix-jaehn-so-close-video|title=NOTD & Felix Jaehn Enlist 'Sports Illustrated' Cover Girl Camille Kostek For 'So Close' Video: Premiere|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Camille Kostek|title=Camille Kostek x So Close Music Video|date=2019-06-26|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TanEY7NHAcA|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"9\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br><ref name=\"SWE\">{{cite web|url=https://swedishcharts.com/search.asp?search=NOTD&cat=s|title=Discography NOTD|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=27 September 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=14 January 2019|accessdate=12 January 2019}}\n* \"Been There Done That\": {{Cite web|url=https://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=57585&pages=|title=australian-charts.com - Forum - ARIA Chartifacts 3-September-2018|date=24 October 2018|website=australian-charts.com|accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL<br>(WA)<br>Tip]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/fr/song/1aa619/NOTD-feat.-Bea-Miller-I-Wanna-Know|title=Discografie Bea Miller}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br><ref name= \"CAN Hot 100\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bea-miller/chart-history/canadian-hot-100|title=Bea Miller Chart History: Canadian Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Tracklisten|DEN]]<br/><ref name=\"DEN\">{{cite web|url=http://danishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Bea+Miller|title=Discography Bea Miller|work=Danish Charts Portal|publisher=Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[VG-lista|NOR]]<br /><ref name=\"NOR\">{{cite web|url=http://norwegiancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=NOTD+feat%2E+Bea+Miller&titel=I+Wanna+Know&cat=s |title=I Wanna Know Chart History |publisher=[[VG-lista]]. Hung Medien|accessdate=14 June 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br><ref name=\"UK Charts\">{{cite web| url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/53462/notd-ft-bea-miller/| title=NOTD ft. Be a Miller Chart History {{!}} UK Official Charts| publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]| accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles|US<br>Bub.]]<br><ref name= \"Bubbling Under\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/bea-miller/chart-history/bubbling-under-hot-100|title=Bea Miller Chart History: Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles|work=Billboard|accessdate=2 May 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Dance Club Songs|US Dance]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bea-miller/chart-history/dance-club-play-songs|title=Bea Miller: Hot Dance Club Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=11 August 2018}}\n* \"So Close\": {{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/felix-jaehn/chart-history/dance-club-play-songs|title=Felix Jaehn Chart History: Dance Club Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=22 February 2019}}\n* \"Wanted\": {{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/daya/chart-history/dance-club-play-songs|title=Daya Chart History: Dance Club Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=23 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Summer of Love\" <br>{{small|(featuring [[Dagny (singer)|Dagny]])}}\n| 2017\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n| rowspan=\"8\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[I Wanna Know (NOTD song)|I Wanna Know]]\" <br>{{small|(featuring [[Bea Miller]])}}\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2018\n| 28 || 18 || 14 || 69 || 40 || 18 || 46 || 23 || 6\n|\n* GLF: Platinum\n* [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]]: 2\u00d7 Platinum<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aria.com.au/pages/SingleAccreds2019.htm|title=ARIA Charts - Accreditations - 2019 Singles|publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association|access-date=2019-01-17}}</ref>\n* MC: 2\u00d7 Platinum \n* RIAA: Platinum<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Been There Done That (NOTD song)|Been There Done That]]\" <br>{{small|(featuring [[Tove Styrke]])}}\n| 69 || 201 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[So Close (NOTD and Felix Jaehn song)|So Close]]\"<br>{{small|(with [[Felix Jaehn]] featuring [[Captain Cuts]] and Georgia Ku)}}\n| 77 || 45 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 1\n|[[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]: Gold<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-06}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Start It Over\"<br>{{small|(featuring CVBZ and [[Shy Martin]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"I Miss Myself\"<br>{{small|(with [[HRVY]])}}\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2019\n| 83 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Keep You Mine\"<br>{{small|(with Shy Martin)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/keep-you-mine-single/1473844063|title=Keep You Mine \u2013 Single by NOTD & Shy Martin|website=Apple Music|accessdate=5 August 2019}}</ref>\n| 45 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Wanted\"<br>{{small|(with [[Daya (singer)|Daya]])}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/wanted-single/1480447765|title=Wanted \u2013 Single by NOTD & Daya|website=Apple Music|accessdate=27 September 2019}}</ref>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 17\n|\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Work\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n|-\n| 2017\n| Electronic Music Awards\n| Remix of the Year\n| Ed Sheeran - \"Shape of You\" (NOTD remix)\n| {{Nom}}<ref name=\"edm award\" />\n|}\n| 2020\n| iHeart Radio Music Awards\n| Dance Song of the Year\n| NOTD & Felix Jaehn - \"So Close\" (ft. Georgia Ku & Captain Cuts)\n| {{Nom}}<ref name=\"edm award\" />\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2017]]\n[[Category:Swedish electronic music groups]]\n[[Category:Swedish musical duos]]\n[[Category:Swedish record producers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = NOTD\n| background = group_or_band\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| alias = \n| origin = \n| genre = \n| years_active = {{start date|2017}}\u2013present\n| label = [[Universal Music Group]]<ref name=\"universal music\">{{cite web |title=NOTD DROP THE OFFICIAL VIDEO FOR BEA MILLER COLLABORATION \"I WANNA KNOW\" {{!}} Umusic |url=http://www.umusic.ca/press-releases/notd-drop-official-video-bea-miller-collaboration-wanna-know/ |website=Umusic |accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref>\n| associated_acts = [[Dagny (singer)|Dagny]] <br> [[Bea Miller]] <br> [[Tove Styrke]]\n| website = \n| current_members =\n* Samuel Brandt (Severo)\n* Tobias Danielsson (ToWonder)\n| past_members    = <!--listed in order of joining per Template:Infobox Musical artist (Boyd/Gray/LeCompt alphabetical by surname\u2014joined at the same time)-->\n}}\n\n'''NOTD''' (pronounced \"noted\") <!--according to iTunes referenced at the end of this sentence--> is a musical production duo from Sweden composed of Tobias Danielsson and Samuel Brandt.<ref name=\"itunes bio\">{{cite web |title=I Wanna Know (feat. Bea Miller) by NOTD |url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/i-wanna-know-feat-bea-miller/1357067762?i=1357067766 |accessdate=18 June 2018 |date=16 March 2018}}</ref> They are best known for their songs \"[[I Wanna Know (NOTD song)|I Wanna Know]]\" featuring [[Bea Miller]] and \"[[So Close (NOTD song)|So Close]]\" with [[Felix Jaehn]] featuring [[Captain Cuts]] and [[Georgia Ku]].\n\n==Background==\nThe duo met on [[Soundcloud]] and began creating remixes together before they found out they would be attending the same high school.<ref name=\"prelude\">{{cite web |last1=Vigil |first1=Dom |title=NOTD releases \"I Wanna Know\" Featuring Bea Miller Remixes |url=https://thepreludepress.com/news/2018/4/27/notd-releases-i-wanna-know-featuring-bea-miller-remixes |website=The Prelude Press |accessdate=20 June 2018}}</ref> The duo chose the name NOTD by combining the last two letters of each of their last names and reversing them.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Espiritu |first1=Camille |title=Music Interview: NOTD - The Young Folks |url=https://www.theyoungfolks.com/music/123134/music-interview-notd/ |website=www.theyoungfolks.com |accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nTheir remix of \"[[Scars to Your Beautiful]]\" by [[Alessia Cara]] was released in 2016.<ref name=\"alessia cara remix\">{{cite web |last1=Bein |first1=Kat |title=Alessia Cara's 'Scars to Your Beautiful' Remixes: Listen to the 7 Best |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7684974/alessia-cara-best-remixes-list |website=Billboard |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> A remix of \"[[Dark Side (Phoebe Ryan song)|Dark Side]]\" by [[Phoebe Ryan]] was released in 2017.<ref name=\"phoebe ryan\">{{cite web |last1=Murray |first1=Robin |title=Premiere: Phoebe Ryan - 'Dark Side' (NOTD Remix) |url=http://clashmusic.com/news/premiere-phoebe-ryan-dark-side-notd-remix |website=Clash Magazine |accessdate=18 June 2018 |language=en}}</ref> Their remix of STANAJ's \"Romantic\", which peaked at #91 in Australia (as \"The Preview EP\") was released on 27 January 2017.<ref>{{Citation|title=Stanaj \u2013 Romantic (NOTD Remix)|url=https://genius.com/Stanaj-romantic-notd-remix-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2018-10-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=48692&pages=5|title=australian-charts.com - Forum - ARIA Chartifacts 17-April-2017|date=17 April 2017|website=australian-charts.com|access-date=2018-10-24}}</ref>  Their remix of \"[[There's Nothing Holdin' Me Back]]\" by [[Shawn Mendes]] was released in May 2017. Their remix of \"[[Shape of You]]\" by [[Ed Sheeran]] received a nomination for an [[Electronic Music Awards|Electronic Music Award]] for Remix of the Year.<ref name=\"edm award\">{{cite web |last1=Rishty |first1=David |title=The Chainsmokers, Justice, Eric Prydz & More Nominated for 2017 Electronic Music Awards |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7896929/electronic-music-awards-nominees-complete-list-2017 |website=Billboard |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> Also in 2017, they released a remix of \"[[Wild Thoughts]]\" by [[DJ Khaled]] and [[Rihanna]], which appeared on Billboard's list of the best remixes of the song.<ref name=\"wild thoughts remix\">{{cite web |last1=Finkelstein |first1=Sabrina |title=The 5 Best DJ Khaled 'Wild Thoughts' Remixes |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7873774/dj-khaled-wild-thoughts-remixes-best |website=Billboard |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> They released their debut single \"Summer of Love\" which features Norwegian singer [[Dagny (singer)|Dagny]] on 11 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rogers |first1=Mandy |title=Listen to \"Summer of Love\" by NOTD ft Dagny - EQ Music Blog |url=https://eqmusicblog.com/listen-summer-love-notd-ft-dagny/ |website=EQ Music Blog |accessdate=10 July 2018 |date=15 August 2017}}</ref> In December 2017, they released a remix of \"[[Tell Me You Love Me (song)|Tell Me You Love Me]]\" by [[Demi Lovato]].<ref name=\"demi lovato\">{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Demi Lovato's \"Tell Me You Love Me\" Gets A Dance Remix From NOTD |url=http://www.idolator.com/7672662/demi-lovato-tell-me-you-love-me-notd-remix?chrome=1 |website=idolator |accessdate=18 June 2018 |date=15 December 2017}}</ref> They also produced a remix of [[Years & Years]]' song \"[[If You're Over Me]]\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Herman |first1=Tamar |title=SHINee's Key Joins Years & Years on Epic 'If You're Over Me' Remix: Listen |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8464216/shinee-key-years-years-if-youre-over-me-remix |website=Billboard |accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nTheir second single \"I Wanna Know\" featuring [[Bea Miller]] was released in March 2018.<ref name=\"fuse\">{{cite web |last1=Gracie |first1=Bianca |title=NOTD & Bea Miller's Moody 'I Wanna Know' Collaboration Is All About Summer Blues: Premiere |url=https://www.fuse.tv/videos/2018/03/notd-bea-miller-i-wanna-know-single-premiere |website=Fuse |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> The song charted in several countries, including [[Australia]], [[Canada]], and [[Sweden]]. Their single \"Been There Done That\" with [[Tove Styrke]] was released in August.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bein |first1=Kat |title=NOTD & Tove Styrke Are Stuck on Love With 'Been There Done That': Listen |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8472119/notd-tove-styrke-been-there-done-that |website=Billboard |accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe duo and [[Felix Jaehn]] released the single \"[[So Close (NOTD and Felix Jaehn song)|So Close]]\", with a music video starring [[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue|''Sports Illustrated'' Swimsuit]] cover girl [[Camille Kostek]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8517789/notd-felix-jaehn-so-close-video|title=NOTD & Felix Jaehn Enlist 'Sports Illustrated' Cover Girl Camille Kostek For 'So Close' Video: Premiere|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Camille Kostek|title=Camille Kostek x So Close Music Video|date=2019-06-26|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TanEY7NHAcA|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"9\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br><ref name=\"SWE\">{{cite web|url=https://swedishcharts.com/search.asp?search=NOTD&cat=s|title=Discography NOTD|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=27 September 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=14 January 2019|accessdate=12 January 2019}}\n* \"Been There Done That\": {{Cite web|url=https://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=57585&pages=|title=australian-charts.com - Forum - ARIA Chartifacts 3-September-2018|date=24 October 2018|website=australian-charts.com|accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL<br>(WA)<br>Tip]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/fr/song/1aa619/NOTD-feat.-Bea-Miller-I-Wanna-Know|title=Discografie Bea Miller}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br><ref name= \"CAN Hot 100\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bea-miller/chart-history/canadian-hot-100|title=Bea Miller Chart History: Canadian Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Tracklisten|DEN]]<br/><ref name=\"DEN\">{{cite web|url=http://danishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Bea+Miller|title=Discography Bea Miller|work=Danish Charts Portal|publisher=Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[VG-lista|NOR]]<br /><ref name=\"NOR\">{{cite web|url=http://norwegiancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=NOTD+feat%2E+Bea+Miller&titel=I+Wanna+Know&cat=s |title=I Wanna Know Chart History |publisher=[[VG-lista]]. Hung Medien|accessdate=14 June 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [