me|Nisekoi]]'' (2014\u20132015)\n* ''[[No Guns Life#Anime|No Guns Life]]'' (2019\u2013present)\n* ''[[Noragami#Anime|Noragami]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Nura:_Rise_of_the_Yokai_Clan#Anime|Nura: Rise of the Yokai Clan]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[One Piece#Anime series|One Piece]]'' (1999\u2013present)\n* ''[[One-Punch Man#Anime|One-Punch Man]]'' (2015\u2013present)\n* ''[[The Ones Within#Anime|The Ones Within]]'' (2019\u2013present)\n* ''[[Ouran High School Host Club#Anime|Ouran High School  Host Club]]'' (2006)\n* ''[[Outlaw Star#Anime|Outlaw Star]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Parasyte#Anime|Parasyte]]'' (2014\u20132015)\n* ''[[Patlabor: The TV Series]]'' (1989\u20131990)\n* ''[[Pet Shop of Horrors#Anime television series|Pet Shop of Horrors]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[Plunderer_(manga)#Anime|Plunderer]]'' (2020\u2013present)\n* ''[[Pop Team Epic#Anime|Pop Team Epic]]'' (2018)\n* ''[[The Prince of Tennis#Anime|The Prince of Tennis]]'' (2001\u20132012)\n* ''[[The Promised Neverland#Anime|The Promised Neverland]]'' (2019\u2013present)\n* ''[[Ranma 1/2#Anime|Ranma 1/2]]'' (1989\u20131992)\n* ''[[Rave Master#Anime|Rave Master]]'' (2001\u20132002)\n* ''[[Revolutionary Girl Utena#Anime (TV series)|Revolutionary Girl Utena]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Ronin Warriors]]'' (1988\u20131989)\n* ''[[Rurouni Kenshin#Anime series|Rurouni Kenshin]]'' (1996\u20131998)\n* ''[[Samurai Deeper Kyo#Anime adaptation|Samurai Deeper Kyo]]'' (2002)\n* ''[[Saiyuki (manga)#Anime|Saiyuki]]'' (2000\u20132017)\n* ''[[Sailor Moon (TV series)|Sailor Moon]]'' (1992\u20131997)\n* ''[[Saint Seiya#Anime|Saint Seiya]]'' (1986\u20131989)\n* ''[[Saint Seiya Omega]]'' (2012\u20132014)\n* ''[[Sazae-san#Anime_series|Sazae-san]]'' (1969\u2013present)\n* ''[[The Seven Deadly Sins (manga)#Anime|The Seven Deadly Sins]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Shaman King#Anime|Shaman King]]'' (2001\u20132002)\n* ''[[Silent Mobius#TV series|Silent Mobius]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Speed Racer#Anime|Speed Racer]]'' (1967\u20131968)\n* ''[[Speed Racer: The Next Generation]]'' (2008\u20132013)\n* ''[[Speed Racer X]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Soul Eater (manga)#Anime|Soul Eater]]'' (2008\u20132009)\n* ''[[Soul Eater Not!#Anime|Soul Eater Not!]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Sword Gai#Anime|Sword Gai: The Animation]]'' (2018)\n* ''[[Tactics (manga)#Anime|Tactics]]'' (2004\u20132005)\n* ''[[Ani_ni_Tsukeru_Kusuri_wa_Nai!#Anime|Take My Brother Away]]'' (2017\u20132019)\n* ''[[Teasing_Master_Takagi-san#Anime|Teasing Master Takagi-san]]'' (2018\u20132019)\n* ''[[Tenjho Tenge#Anime|Tenjho Tenge]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[Toilet-Bound_Hanako-kun#Anime|Toilet-Bound Hanako-kun]]'' (2020\u2013present)\n* ''[[Tokko (manga)#Anime|Tokko]]'' (2006)\n* ''[[Tokyo Ghoul#Anime|Tokyo Ghoul]]'' (2018)\n* ''[[Trigun#Anime|Trigun]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Kinnikuman#Television series|Ultimate Muscle]]'' (2002\u20132006)\n* ''[[UQ_Holder!#Anime|UQ Holder!]]'' (2017\u2013\u20132018)\n* ''[[Urusei Yatsura#Anime|Urusei Yatsura]]'' (1981\u20131986)\n* ''[[Vinland Saga (manga)#Anime|Vinland Saga]]'' (2019\u2013present)\n* ''[[We_Never_Learn#Anime|We Never Learn]]'' (2019)\n* ''[[Wild 7#Anime|Wild 7]]'' (2002)\n* ''[[You're Under Arrest (manga)#Anime|You're Under Arrest]]'' (2007\u20132008)\n* ''[[Your_Lie_in_April#Anime|Your Lie in April]]'' (2014\u20132015)\n* ''[[Yu Yu Hakusho#Anime|Yu Yu Hakusho]]'' (1992\u20131994)\n* ''[[Zatch Bell!#Anime|Zatch Bell!]]'' (2003\u20132006)\n\n==Series about comics==\n* ''[[Alien Dawn]]'' (2013\u20132014) \u2013 Series about a boy investigating alien activity and conspiracy theories that inspired his missing father's comic book.\n* ''[[Almost Heroes (TV series)|Almost Heroes]]'' (2011) \u2013 Sitcom about two brothers running their late father's comic book store.\n* ''[[American Horror Story: Cult]]'' (2017) \u2013 A part of the ''[[American Horror Story]]'' anthology.  It features the character Twisty the Clown in a comic book.\n* ''[[Best.Worst.Weekend.Ever.]]'' (2018) \u2013 A group of teenagers attempt to sneak into a comic book convention to show their homemade comic book to their favorite comic book author.\n* ''[[Big Bad Beetleborgs]]'' (1996\u20131998) \u2013 A group of kids are transformed into their favorite comic book superheoes.\n* ''[[The Big Bang Theory]]'' (2007\u20132019) \u2013 Most of the main characters are comic book fans.  Nearly every episode references comic books.\n* ''[[Bless the Harts]]'' (2019\u2013present) \u2013 One of the main characters, Violet Hart, is an aspiring artist who makes her own comics.\n* ''[[Blood Ties (TV series)|Blood Ties]]'' (2007) \u2013 The main protagonist, Henry Fitzroy, works as a graphic novelist.\n* ''[[Bob (TV series)|Bob]]'' (1992\u20131993) \u2013 Sitcom about a comic book creator.\n* ''[[The Cape (2011 TV series)|The Cape]]'' (2011) \u2013 An honest cop becomes a superhero based on his son's favorite comic book character.\n* ''[[Caroline in the City]]'' (1995\u20131999) \u2013 Sitcom about a comic strip artist.\n* ''[[The Casagrandes]]'' (2019\u2013present) \u2013 Like its predecessor, ''[[The Loud House]]'', the series' background art is heavily influenced by comic strips.\n* ''[[The Comic Artist and His Assistants#Anime|The Comic Artist and His Assistants: The Animation]]'' (2014) \u2013Anime about a manga author.\n* ''[[Comic Book Men]]'' (2012\u20132018) \u2013 A reality-tv series centering on [[Jay and Silent Bob's Secret Stash]]: a comic book store owned by filmmaker [[Kevin Smith]].\n* ''[[Comic Girls#Anime|Comic Girls]]'' (2018) \u2013 Anime about a group of girls determined to make the best manga.\n* ''[[Comic_Party#Anime|Comic Party]]'' (2001) \u2013 Anime about two friends who visit a Comic Party Convention. \n* ''[[The Comic Strip (TV series)|The Comic Strip]]'' (1987) \u2013 Animated series featuring segments of original cartoons in the form of a comic strip.\n* ''[[Con Man (web series)|Con Man]]'' (2015\u20132017) \u2013 Web comedy about a struggling actor eking out a living by attending comic book conventions.\n* ''[[Corner Gas]]'' (2004\u20132009) \u2013 The main character is an avid comic book fan.\n* ''[[Creepshow (TV series)|Creepshow]]'' (2019) \u2013 Horror anthology centering on a comic book.\n* ''[[Dark Oracle]]'' (2004\u20132006) \u2013 Teen drama centering on a comic book.\n* ''[[Detention (TV series)|Detention]]'' (1999\u20132000) \u2013 One of the main characters, Jim Kim, is an obsessed comic book fan.  He references comic books in each episode.\n* ''[[Duck Dodgers (TV series)|Duck Dodgers]]'' (2003\u20132005) \u2013 Parody of the comic strip ''[[Buck Rodgers]]''.\n* ''[[Doug (TV series)|Doug]]'' (1991\u20131999) \u2013 The main protagonist, Doug, aspires to be a comic book artist.  He draws his own comic book featuring his alter-ego, Quilman.\n* ''[[The Epic Tales of Captain Underpants]]'' (2018\u2013present) \u2013 Series about two boys who make their own comics.  They hypnotize their principal into becoming their comic creation.\n* ''[[Fairly OddParents]]'' (2001\u20132017) \u2013 The series features a reoccurring character, the Crimson Chin: a comic book superhero.\n* ''[[Fanboy & Chum Chum]]'' (2009\u20132012) \u2013 Animated series about two comic book fans.\n* ''[[Geeking Out]]'' (2016) \u2013 Series exploring comic books and other forms of nerd culture.\n* ''[[Heroes (American TV series)|Heroes]]'' (2006\u20132010) \u2013 Series told in the form of a comic books.\n* ''[[Heroes Reborn (miniseries)|Heroes Reborn]]'' (2015) \u2013 Series told in the form of a comic book.\n* ''[[High School USA!]]'' (2013\u20132015) \u2013 Parody of [[Archie Comics]]''.\n* ''[[Kirk (TV series)|Kirk]]'' (1995\u20131997) \u2013 Sitcom about an illustrator taking care of his family.\n* ''[[The Loud House]]'' (2016\u2013present)\u2013 The main character, Lincoln Loud, is an avid comic book fan.  The series' background art is heavily inspired by comic strips.\n* ''[[McGee and Me!]]'' (1989\u20131995) \u2013 Series about an aspiring cartoonist having adventures with his creation while growing in his Christian faith.\n* ''[[Mighty Med]]'' (2013\u20132015) \u2013 Sitcom about two teenaged comic fans who work as doctors in a superhero hospital.\n* ''[[Mission Hill (TV series)|Mission Hill]]'' (1999\u20132002) \u2013 Animated sitcom about an aspiring cartoonist who lives with his teenaged brother in a big city-loft.\n* ''[[Once a Hero]]'' (1987) \u2013 Series about a comic book superhero coming to life.\n* ''[[The Replacements (TV series)|The Replacements]]'' (2006\u20132009) \u2013 Two orphans use an ad in a comic book to replace things.\n* ''[[Recess (TV series)|Recess]]'' (1997\u20132001) \u2013 The main characters are fans of the comic book ''Senor Fusion''.\n* ''[[Rocko's Modern Life]]'' (1993\u20131996) \u2013 The main protagonist, Rocko, works at a comic book shop.\n* ''[[The Simpsons]]'' (1989\u2013present) \u2013 The series features a reoccurring character, [[Comic Book Guy]].  He is a comic book collector who owns the local comic book store.  He often criticizes and references comic books.\n* ''[[The Troop]]'' (2009\u20132013) \u2013 One of the main characters is an aspiring comic artist.\n* ''[[Queer as Folk (American TV series)|Queer as Folk]]'' (2000\u20132005) \u2013 One of the characters, [[Michael Novotny]] is an avid comic book fan.  He reads comics, attends conventions, and eventually owns a comic store and writes his own comic.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of comic-based television episodes directed by women]]\n* [[List of superhero television series]]\n* [[List of television programs based on video games]]\n* [[List of comics based on television programs]]\n* [[List of films based on comics]]\n* [[List of films based on comic strips]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Television programs based on comics|*List]]\n[[Category:Lists of works based on comics|Television programs]]\n[[Category:Lists of television series based on works|Comics]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|television programs based on comic books|comic strips|List of television series based on comic strips}}\n{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{more citations needed|date=May 2016}}\n\nThis is a '''list of television shows based on comics'''.\n\n==DC and Marvel==\n\nAs so many [[DC Comics|DC]] and [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] comic books have been adapted into television shows, they have separate entries:\n* [[List of television series based on DC Comics]]\n* [[List of television series based on Marvel Comics]]\n\n==Independents==\n* [[List of television series and films based on Archie Comics]]\n* [[List of television series based on Dark Horse Comics]]\n* [[List of television series and films based on Harvey Comics publications]]\n* [[List of television series and films based on Image Comics]]\n* [[List of unproduced Image Comics projects]]\n* [[List of TV series based on French-language comics]]\n* [[List of television series based on comic strips]]\n\n==Live-action==\n* ''[[30 Days of Night: Blood Trails]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[30 Days of Night: Dust to Dust]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Agua Bendita]]'' (Philippines, 2010)\n* ''[[Andres de Saya]]'' (Philippines, 2011)\n* ''[[Ang Babaeng Hinugot sa Aking Tadyang]]'' (Philippines, 2009)\n* ''[[Ang Panday (2005 TV series)|Ang Panday]]'' (Philippines, 2005\u20132006)\n* ''[[Ang Panday (2016 TV series)|Ang Panday]]'' (Philippines, 2016)\n* ''[[Bakekang]]'' (Philippines, 2006\u20132007)\n* ''[[Basahang Ginto]]'' (Philippines, 2010)\n* ''[[Bewegte M\u00e4nner]]'' (Germany, 2003\u20132005)\n* ''[[Blusang Itim]]'' (Philippines, 2011)\n* ''[[Captain Barbell (TV series)|Captain Barbell]]'' (Philippines, 2006\u20132007)\n* ''[[Captain Barbell (2011 TV series)|Captain Barbell]]'' (Philippines, 2011)\n* ''[[Click (comics)|Click]]'' (Italy, 1997)\n* ''[[Cybersix#Live-action series|Cybersix]]'' (Argentina, 1995)\n* ''[[Darna (2005 TV series)|Darna]]'' (Philippines, 2005)\n* ''[[Darna (2009 TV series)|Darna]]'' (Philippines, 2009\u20132010)\n* ''[[Daybreak (2019 TV series)|Daybreak]]'' (2019)\n* ''[[Dyesebel (2008 TV series)|Dyesebel]]'' (Philippines, 2008)\n* ''[[D