o|year=2007|publisher=University of Nebraska Press|location=Lincoln}}; a standard scholarly biography; [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=114943778 online]\n* Fowler, Will. ''Mexico in the Age of Proposals, 1821\u20131853'' (1998)\n* Fowler, Will. ''Tornel and Santa Anna: The Writer and the Caudillo, Mexico, 1795\u20131853'' (2000) [https://www.amazon.com/Tornel-Santa-Anna-1795-1853-Contributions/dp/0313309140/ excerpt and text search]\n* Green, Stanley C. ''The Mexican Republic: The First Decade 1823\u20131832''. Pittsburgh: University of Pittsburgh Press 1987\n* [[Hardin, Stephen L.]], and McBride, Angus. ''The Alamo 1836: Santa Anna's Texas Campaign'' (2001) [https://www.amazon.com/Alamo-1836-Santa-Annas-Campaign/dp/1841760900/ excerpt and text search]\n* Jackson, Jack. \"Santa Anna's 1836 Campaign: Was It Directed Toward Ethnic Cleansing?\" ''Journal of South Texas'' (March 2002) 15#1 pp.&nbsp;10\u201337; argues that yes it was\n* Jackson, Jack, and Wheat, John. ''Almonte's Texas'', Texas State Historical Assoc.\n*[[Enrique Krauze|Krauze, Enrique]], ''Mexico: Biography of Power''. New York: HarperCollins 1997. {{ISBN|0-06-016325-9}}\n* {{citation|last=Lord|first=Walter|author-link=Walter Lord|title=A Time to Stand|publisher=[[University of Nebraska Press]]|year=1961|location=Lincoln, NE|isbn=0-8032-7902-7|url=https://archive.org/details/timetostand00lord}}, popular history\n* Mabry, Donald J., [https://web.archive.org/web/20101216150941/http://historicaltextarchive.com/sections.php?action=read&artid=159 \"Antonio Lopez de Santa Anna\"], 2 November 2008; essay by scholar\n* Roberts, Randy & Olson, James S., ''A Line in the Sand: The Alamo in Blood and Memory'' (2002)\n* Santoni, Pedro; ''Mexicans at Arms-Puro Federalist and the Politics of War'' TCU Press; {{ISBN missing}}\n* Schein, Robert L. ''Santa Anna: A Curse Upon Mexico'' (2003) [https://www.amazon.com/Santa-Anna-Mexico-Military-Profiles/dp/1574885464/ excerpt and text search]\n* Suchlicki, Jaime. \"Mexico: Montezuma to the Rise of Pan\", Potomac Books: Washington DC, 1996.\n{{div col end|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Antonio L\u00f3pez de Santa Anna}}\n{{EB9 Poster|Santa Anna, Antonio Lopez de|Antonio L\u00f3pez de Santa Anna}}\n*[http://texashistory.unt.edu/browse/subject/People/Individuals/Antonio_Lopez_de_Santa_Anna/ Santa Anna Letters on the ''Portal to Texas History'']\n*[https://archive.is/20130705193718/http://library.uta.edu/usmexicowar/biographyresult.php?bio_id=10 Antonio L\u00f3pez de Santa Anna] in [http://library.uta.edu/usmexicowar/ A Continent Divided: The U.S. \u2013 Mexico War], Center for Greater Southwestern Studies, the University of Texas at Arlington\n*[https://tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/fsa29 ''The Handbook of Texas Online'': Antonio Lopez de Santa Anna]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20051113101628/http://www.lib.utexas.edu/benson/Mex_Archives/Santa_Anna.html Benson Latin American Collection \u2013 Antonio L\u00f3pez de Santa Anna Collection]\n*Sketch of [http://texashistory.unt.edu/widgets/pager.php?object_id=meta-pth-5828&recno=177&path=meta-pth-5828.tkl Santa Anna] from [https://web.archive.org/web/20080723155832/http://texashistory.unt.edu/permalink/meta-pth-5828 ''A pictorial history of Texas, from the earliest visits of European adventurers to A.D. 1879''], hosted by the [http://texashistory.unt.edu/ Portal to Texas History].\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060210051329/http://www.archontology.org/nations/mex/mex2/santa_anna1.php ''Archontology.org, Home \u00bb Nations \u00bb Mexico \u00bb Heads of State \u00bb L\u00d3PEZ de SANTA ANNA, Antonio'']\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060904235516/http://tides.sfasu.edu/AN18/SHHI_29.php?culture=2&chrono=5&index=0 Texas Prisoners in Mexico 3 August 1843] From [https://web.archive.org/web/20060822022222/http://tides.sfasu.edu/ Texas Tides]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-off}}\n{{S-bef|rows=4|before=[[Valent\u00edn G\u00f3mez Far\u00edas]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|President of Mexico]]|years=17 May \u2013 4 June 1833}}\n{{s-aft|rows=3|after=[[Valent\u00edn G\u00f3mez Far\u00edas]]}}\n|-\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|President of Mexico]]|years=18 June \u2013 5 July 1833}}\n|-\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|President of Mexico]]|years=27 October \u2013 15 December 1833}}\n|-\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|President of Mexico]]|years=24 April 1834 \u2013 27 January 1835}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Miguel Barrag\u00e1n]]}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[Anastasio Bustamante]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|Interim President of Mexico]]|years=20 March \u2013 10 July 1839}}\n{{s-aft|rows=2|after=[[Nicol\u00e1s Bravo]]}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[Francisco Javier Echeverr\u00eda]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|Provisional President of Mexico]]|years=10 October 1841 \u2013 26 October 1842}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[Nicol\u00e1s Bravo]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|Provisional President of Mexico]]|years=4 March \u2013 4 October 1843}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Valent\u00edn Canalizo]]}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[Valent\u00edn Canalizo]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|Provisional President of Mexico]]|years=4 June \u2013 12 September 1844}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Jos\u00e9 Joaqu\u00edn de Herrera]]}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[Valent\u00edn G\u00f3mez Far\u00edas]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|Interim President of Mexico]]|years=21 March \u2013 2 April 1847}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Pedro Mar\u00eda de Anaya]]}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[Pedro Mar\u00eda de Anaya]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|Interim President of Mexico]]|years=20 May \u2013 15 September 1847}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Manuel de la Pe\u00f1a y Pe\u00f1a]]}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|before=[[Manuel Mar\u00eda Lombardini]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Presidents of Mexico|Dictator-President of Mexico]]|years=20 April 1853 \u2013 9 August 1855}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Mart\u00edn Carrera]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{MexPostIndPresidents}}\n{{Battle of the Alamo}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Santa Anna, Antonio Lopez De}}\n[[Category:Presidents of Mexico]]\n[[Category:Vice Presidents of Mexico]]\n[[Category:Leaders who took power by coup]]\n[[Category:Mexican generals]]\n[[Category:Mexican military personnel of the Mexican\u2013American War]]\n[[Category:People from Staten Island]]\n[[Category:1794 births]]\n[[Category:1876 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Mexican people]]\n[[Category:19th-century Mexican politicians]]\n[[Category:19th-century rulers in North America]]\n[[Category:1830s in Mexico]]\n[[Category:Mexican amputees]]\n[[Category:Independent Mexico]]\n[[Category:Generalissimos]]\n[[Category:Governors of Veracruz]]\n[[Category:Governors of Yucat\u00e1n (state)]]\n[[Category:Mexican exiles]]\n[[Category:Mexican people of Spanish descent]]\n[[Category:Candidates in the 1833 Mexican presidential election]]\n[[Category:Recipients of Mexican presidential pardons]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Xalapa]]\n[[Category:People of Mexican side in the Texas Revolution]]\n[[Category:People of the Mexican War of Independence]]\n[[Category:Second French intervention in Mexico]]\n[[Category:19th-century Mexican military personnel]]\n", "name_user": "Rontrigger", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePresident for the last time, 1853-55", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antonio_L%C3%B3pez_de_Santa_Anna"}
